column5: I may want to wait a day or 2 before I go out there here is a link to the website that posts them http://coastwatch.glerl.noaa.gov/modis/mod...io.143.250m.jpg
Wha?!?  That's showing Cooke's Bay wide open?  Is that for real?
Is the boat  put away Terry?  If so,we can call Wayne and go out newyears day.
Well, that shoots Friday's plans all to H E double hockey sticks! Thanks for the heads up Terry, the Perch will live another day... and so will I! HH

Thats sucks big time terry !!!! man on the link picture you can see the mud lines on lake ontario,and lake erie is chocolate milk color !!! it looks like scugog is still frozen excepth for the area around view lake and the river entrance !!! but like you said simcoe does not look good at all,and it looks like only half of cooks bay is solid
Friday still may be good  don't give up hope for cooks bay virgina beach and beaverton kempenfelt bay is a right off so no whitiefish but perch could happen
Wheres Cudz when I need him.LOL   Hey Terry If are willing to punch holes along the river edge,I,ll walk behind you and flip them.
Thanks for the update Terry.  I was hoping to go out for lakers on friday.  I dont think it is going to get cold enough to make that much ice though.

well misfish bass are out of season, but there could be crappie along those shorelines...I will wear my snowshoes glen, a few days ago I thought that at lest kempenfelt would be ok for lakers and whities, but  doesn't look good at all  I do have my folding boat if the winds die down

hey terry  I think the ice is still there the picture is just reflecting off water on the ice here is a picture later in the day  i does appear to be water on the ice or black ice or shadow of the clouds leving dark spots  even in the earlier shot it shows scugog almost wide open on the viewlake side and the later shot below shows it all tight with no open areas  look below  http://coastwatch.glerl.noaa.gov/modis/mod...io.143.250m.jpg
Y'all wear your floater suit or PFD (just in case) now ya heah?
Well maybe it's reflecting off the shiny surface, check this guys real photos:  http://www.lakesimcoemessageboard.com/inde...;id_dbase=93391
What ever it takes to get a report ,so you dont grow old and missing a miss fish report Dawg.
